article.headline: Oral Roberts 68, S. Dakota St. 63
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Michael Craion made three free throws, pulled down a rebound and came up with a steal, all in the final 31 seconds, to help Oral Roberts hold on for a 68-63 victory over South Dakota State on Saturday night. Dominique Morrison led Oral Roberts with 21 points, followed by Craion with 16 as the Golden Eagles (13-10, 8-3 Summit) salvaged a split of their season series with the Jackrabbits (11-11, 7-4). Clint Sargent had 21 points, including six 3-pointers, and Nate Wolters scored 17 for South Dakota State. The Golden Eagles trailed 41-37 early in the second half before going on a 13-0 run to take a 50-41 lead they never relinquished.
